IRCMON
======

Dependencys
-----------

* node.js: http://nodejs.org/
  for the server

* openssl
  node.js needs openssl for hashing


Installation
------------

1. $ node server.js

2. put client.html somewhere in your httpd's htdocs directory

3. make sure your httpd redirects requests to data.js in the same directory to
   localhost:50005.

   With lighttpd:
     $HTTP["url"] =~ "^/webzeug/ircmon/data.js" {
       proxy-core.protocol = "http"
       proxy-core.backends = ( "127.0.0.1:50005" )
     }

4. Open client.html in your browser


